1
00:00:12,916 --> 00:00:15,125
[sighs]

2
00:00:22,291 --> 00:00:25,125
[exhales]

3
00:00:28,208 --> 00:00:31,208
[SERAFINA] Where am I?
A dungeon?

4
00:00:32,625 --> 00:00:34,166
I've been shackled!

5
00:00:34,375 --> 00:00:35,458
My feet too?

6
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,000
[shackles rattling]

7
00:00:38,208 --> 00:00:39,416
And a collar.

8
00:00:40,125 --> 00:00:41,583
[shackles rattling]

9
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,625
I see. We lost the battle.

10
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:48,333
And I've been taken prisoner.

11
00:00:50,041 --> 00:00:52,291
So the barbarians
were victorious!

12
00:01:05,750 --> 00:01:08,458
ANNO DRACONIS
IN THE EAST OF THE CONTINENT-—

13
00:01:08,666 --> 00:01:10,583
BARBARIAN TERRITORY

14
00:01:15,916 --> 00:01:18,041
[dramatic music]

15
00:01:18,041 --> 00:01:21,208
[shouting]

16
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:25,291
[BOTH grunting]

17
00:01:38,458 --> 00:01:41,291
[ILLDOREN LIEUTENANT]
Rifle brigade, ready arms!

18
00:01:41,916 --> 00:01:43,500
[shouting]

19
00:01:43,916 --> 00:01:45,416
[ILLDOREN LIEUTENANT] Fire!

20
00:01:46,416 --> 00:01:47,875
[gasps]

21
00:01:49,291 --> 00:01:51,208
[ILLDOREN LIEUTENANT]
Reload weapons!

22
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:54,291
There are too many!

23
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:56,500
Our forces are being
overwhelmed, Captain!

24
00:01:56,708 --> 00:01:58,083
The volunteers have fallen

25
00:01:58,083 --> 00:02:00,291
and the front line
of our left wing's collapsed!

26
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:01,625
Compose yourself!

27
00:02:01,625 --> 00:02:03,583
You are a knight
of the Illdoren Kingdom!

28
00:02:04,041 --> 00:02:05,208
Have the left wing pull back!

29
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:07,125
[SERAFINA]
Extend the center and right

30
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:09,166
outwards into
a partial wing formation!

31
00:02:09,375 --> 00:02:10,583
We have to retreat

32
00:02:10,583 --> 00:02:12,208
but we can deflect
these savages' attacks

33
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:13,875
while doing so!

34
00:02:15,125 --> 00:02:16,458
[exhales]

35
00:02:17,041 --> 00:02:20,250
[epic battle music]

36
00:02:23,333 --> 00:02:25,291
Even if we manage
to break past their army,

37
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:27,458
we've lost far
too many soldiers.

38
00:02:28,041 --> 00:02:30,208
[SERAFINA] Any further losses
will affect our chances

39
00:02:30,416 --> 00:02:31,583
of returning home,

40
00:02:31,583 --> 00:02:33,416
and the seventeenth
Eastern Expedition

41
00:02:33,625 --> 00:02:35,125
will end after seven years.

42
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:39,166
I have to save as many
of my comrades as possible.

43
00:02:39,416 --> 00:02:41,166
[gasps]

44
00:02:41,166 --> 00:02:44,291
[dramatic music]

45
00:02:46,916 --> 00:02:49,458
[shouting]

46
00:02:53,041 --> 00:02:54,458
[stunned]

47
00:03:00,875 --> 00:03:02,750
You're wearing a crystal helmet.

48
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:04,291
So you must be the general.

49
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,708
[VEOR] Good,
because I've grown tired

50
00:03:06,916 --> 00:03:08,416
of facing these foot soldiers.

51
00:03:09,458 --> 00:03:11,458
Would you care
to give me a real challenge?

52
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,875
He couldn't have appeared
at a worse time.

53
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,458
[SERAFINA]
But if I ignore someone

54
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:19,291
whose blade slices
through armor like paper,

55
00:03:19,291 --> 00:03:20,916
the withdrawal will fail.

56
00:03:22,041 --> 00:03:23,916
Perhaps he's overconfident.

57
00:03:24,125 --> 00:03:25,875
If it's individual combat
he wants,

58
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:27,333
I won't refuse.

59
00:03:27,541 --> 00:03:29,208
-[SERAFINA] Lieutenant!
-Yes, Captain.

60
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,833
Regardless
of what happens to me,

61
00:03:32,416 --> 00:03:33,875
get our men home

62
00:03:34,083 --> 00:03:36,166
and tell my brother
that I gave my life

63
00:03:36,375 --> 00:03:38,875
in service to my homeland!

64
00:03:39,083 --> 00:03:40,416
[SERAFINA shouts]

65
00:03:44,416 --> 00:03:47,166
[grunting]

66
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:50,875
[VEOR shouting]

67
00:03:54,291 --> 00:03:55,750
[grunting]

68
00:04:03,208 --> 00:04:05,000
Princess Wysteresia!

69
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,208
Lend me your strength
for this fight!

70
00:04:08,583 --> 00:04:11,750
[epic battle music]

71
00:04:12,166 --> 00:04:15,000
[BOTH shouting]

72
00:04:25,125 --> 00:04:26,625
This is it for me.

73
00:04:27,041 --> 00:04:28,625
That was fun.

74
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:31,291
There aren't many who can last
that long against me.

75
00:04:31,291 --> 00:04:33,166
[tense]

76
00:04:33,708 --> 00:04:35,458
-Just do it.
-[VEOR] I don't think so.

77
00:04:35,875 --> 00:04:37,291
[grinning]

78
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,291
Why kill you? It's pointless.

79
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:42,000
Instead.

80
00:04:42,416 --> 00:04:44,875
[VEOR] I'd rather take you
as my prize.

81
00:04:45,291 --> 00:04:48,000
Besides, I could think
of far more pleasant uses

82
00:04:48,208 --> 00:04:49,833
for that body of yours.

83
00:04:50,041 --> 00:04:53,041
[horrified]

84
00:04:56,708 --> 00:04:58,208
I remember now.

85
00:04:58,416 --> 00:05:00,000
After I was defeated,

86
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,750
he took me away
as his spoils of war.

87
00:05:04,125 --> 00:05:05,583
Wait, will he make me a peasant

88
00:05:05,791 --> 00:05:07,333
and put me to work
in the fields?

89
00:05:07,625 --> 00:05:09,500
[gasps]

90
00:05:09,708 --> 00:05:12,500
Or even worse, torture me
to acquire valuable information?

91
00:05:12,708 --> 00:05:14,125
[SERAFINA]
He could've killed me,

92
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:15,583
but I was taken instead.

93
00:05:15,583 --> 00:05:17,500
That must have been done
for a reason.

94
00:05:17,708 --> 00:05:18,916
[gasps]

95
00:05:19,291 --> 00:05:21,041
I could think
of far more pleasant uses

96
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:22,833
for that body of yours.

97
00:05:23,041 --> 00:05:24,500
[gasps]

98
00:05:24,708 --> 00:05:27,291
Oh no. He's planning
to use my body?

99
00:05:27,291 --> 00:05:29,000
Expeditionary captain or not,

100
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,458
I'm still a woman.

101
00:05:30,666 --> 00:05:32,000
[gasps]

102
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,166
[BARBARIAN'S menacing laughter]

103
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:36,416
[SERAFINA] They must mean
to use me for sport!

104
00:05:38,583 --> 00:05:40,583
I can't think
of a worse situation

105
00:05:40,791 --> 00:05:43,041
for an unmarried noblewoman
to find herself in!

106
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:46,708
Do these ogres have no decency?

107
00:05:46,708 --> 00:05:48,291
[gasps] And my troops!

108
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,416
What has become of the men
who fought alongside me?

109
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:53,250
[SERAFINA] I was bested quickly,

110
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:55,625
so I couldn't possibly have
bought them enough time

111
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,583
to organize
a successful retreat!

112
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,833
And if the rear
managed to get away,

113
00:06:00,041 --> 00:06:02,208
the front lines were likely
broken to pieces.

114
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:08,000
Which means, their corpses
are rotting on the battlefield.

115
00:06:08,208 --> 00:06:09,625
[tense]

116
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:12,125
But more pressing
than even that.

117
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:15,583
[solemn music]

118
00:06:16,916 --> 00:06:18,708
If we can't wrest
the eastern lands

119
00:06:18,708 --> 00:06:20,750
from the barbarians' control,

120
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:23,208
the people of the capital
will starve.

121
00:06:24,875 --> 00:06:28,500
[solemn music]

122
00:06:31,583 --> 00:06:34,000
It's my duty as a noble
to safeguard their livelihood,

123
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:35,750
and I failed them!

124
00:06:37,458 --> 00:06:40,000
[CERSEI] Taking the "“noble"”
part literally, are we?

125
00:06:41,875 --> 00:06:43,166
Who's there?

126
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:44,875
[sighs]

127
00:06:45,416 --> 00:06:46,708
Calm yourself.

128
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,500
My name is Cersei,

129
00:06:48,708 --> 00:06:50,333
servant of the man
who captured you.

130
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:52,583
[tense]

131
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:55,583
[SERAFINA] Servant, you say?

132
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:59,500
And you're no doubt here
to press me for intelligence.

133
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:01,208
Intelligence?

134
00:07:01,916 --> 00:07:03,750
No, I don't know
what that means.

135
00:07:05,041 --> 00:07:07,041
Don't lie to me, barbarian!

136
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:08,833
You clearly came
armed with instruments

137
00:07:09,041 --> 00:07:11,000
of some sort
to force me to talk!

138
00:07:12,416 --> 00:07:15,000
[CERSEI] All you need to know
is I was given one command.

139
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:19,041
And that is to make certain
that you, his trophy,

140
00:07:19,250 --> 00:07:21,416
are in a condition
that is to his liking.

141
00:07:21,708 --> 00:07:23,000
Trophy?

142
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,541
Hey, what do you think
you're doing?

143
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,041
Hold still.

144
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:33,833
If you struggle,
it'll just make this harder.

145
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:35,916
[tense]

146
00:07:36,916 --> 00:07:38,500
And so it begins.

147
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:40,541
But to restrain me like this?

148
00:07:40,750 --> 00:07:42,875
How brutal are
their torture methods?

149
00:07:43,166 --> 00:07:45,000
No matter. Remain strong.

150
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,625
[SERAFINA] Don't give them
the intel or the satisfaction!

151
00:07:51,708 --> 00:07:53,166
[VEOR] Mmm.

152
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,500
She will likely be awake by now.

153
00:07:58,416 --> 00:08:00,708
Here I come,
my beautiful treasure.

154
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:06,750
[SERAFINA panting]

155
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:15,708
How shameful!
To debase me in such a way.

156
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:21,750
All done.

157
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:23,916
Now you no longer
stink of warfare.

158
00:08:24,125 --> 00:08:25,875
What sort of torture is this?

159
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:28,458
The kind
that you needed, I think.

160
00:08:28,916 --> 00:08:30,333
You smelled bad.

161
00:08:30,541 --> 00:08:32,500
Your body was covered
in blood and filth.

162
00:08:32,708 --> 00:08:35,416
-I was simply cleaning it off.
-What?

163
00:08:35,416 --> 00:08:37,625
And I have to admit,
I was quite impressed

164
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:40,541
when I heard about you
exchanging blows with my master.

165
00:08:41,708 --> 00:08:44,125
[CERSEI] I expected to see
a brutish woman when I arrived,

166
00:08:44,625 --> 00:08:46,041
but you're certainly not that.

167
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,291
For someone
who is so adept at fighting,

168
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:52,750
you possess
an undeniably feminine figure.

169
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:54,833
Don't mock me,

170
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,916
I'm a knight and have no use
for femininity!

171
00:08:57,125 --> 00:08:58,416
[CERSEI] Well, that's nice.

172
00:08:58,416 --> 00:09:00,750
But it doesn't matter
how you feel about it.

173
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:03,000
What matters is,
my master has decided

174
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:04,500
that you are suitable.

175
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:07,583
Suitable for what, exactly?

176
00:09:07,791 --> 00:09:10,041
Would telling you
make it any easier, I wonder?

177
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,750
No.

178
00:09:12,416 --> 00:09:14,416
Ultimately, knowing
would change nothing.

179
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:17,666
Because either way, Knight,
you aren't leaving here.

180
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:19,125
[gasps]

181
00:09:19,583 --> 00:09:20,666
No, wait!

182
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:22,541
What are you doing now?

183
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:25,875
Oh, just applying
the finishing touches.

184
00:09:27,666 --> 00:09:30,125
[struggling]

185
00:09:33,208 --> 00:09:34,833
I must endure.

186
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:36,500
[flinching]

187
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:39,125
[shrieking]

188
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:51,916
Huh?

189
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,500
Why are you clothing me?

190
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,875
[SERAFINA] Is this truly not
an interrogation then?

191
00:10:00,625 --> 00:10:03,291
[sniffing] Scented oils?

192
00:10:03,583 --> 00:10:05,541
Why waste them
on a prisoner of war?

193
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,291
This doesn't make sense.

194
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,750
Giving me fresh clothes
with a delightful aroma,

195
00:10:10,958 --> 00:10:12,541
what am I being prepared for?

196
00:10:13,583 --> 00:10:15,291
Well, I would say

197
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:16,875
you're looking presentable now.

198
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:19,750
[SERAFINA] I don't know
what's going on.

199
00:10:19,958 --> 00:10:22,458
Is this some weird ritual
for prisoners?

200
00:10:22,916 --> 00:10:24,458
Don't tell me.

201
00:10:24,666 --> 00:10:27,583
[VEOR shouting]

202
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:29,833
What was that? Thunder or?

203
00:10:30,375 --> 00:10:32,708
No. Only he could emit
a shout like that one.

204
00:10:32,916 --> 00:10:33,958
[gasps]

205
00:10:35,875 --> 00:10:37,458
So it's him.

206
00:10:39,583 --> 00:10:42,708
[dramatic music]

207
00:10:47,625 --> 00:10:48,958
This is a sight.

208
00:10:49,625 --> 00:10:51,416
From knights armor
to lady's dress.

209
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,875
It's like night and day,
Crystal Helmet.

210
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:06,416
[nervous]

211
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:09,250
There was no time
for a proper introduction

212
00:11:09,458 --> 00:11:10,541
during the battle.

213
00:11:10,541 --> 00:11:12,250
I am the proud scion
and successor

214
00:11:12,458 --> 00:11:14,375
of our Great Chief
Uldyn One Eye:

215
00:11:14,583 --> 00:11:16,333
Thundering Voice Veor.

216
00:11:17,083 --> 00:11:19,875
He's somehow even
more massive than I realized.

217
00:11:20,083 --> 00:11:22,458
And those searing golden eyes.

218
00:11:22,875 --> 00:11:24,666
He can't be human.

219
00:11:24,916 --> 00:11:26,875
It's clear to me now.

220
00:11:27,083 --> 00:11:28,916
I know what you people want.

221
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,791
[SERAFINA] My grandfather was
part of the Eastern Expedition

222
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,458
20 years ago.

223
00:11:36,750 --> 00:11:38,291
His story sounded
like fairy tales,

224
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:40,625
but I can see
that they were true.

225
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:46,416
[laughing]

226
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:52,500
Your inhuman eyes
are brimming with pure evil!

227
00:11:53,708 --> 00:11:57,250
Listen! I am of the Lavillant
Margraves of Illdoren,

228
00:11:57,458 --> 00:11:59,166
daughter to
the former lord, Mattius,

229
00:11:59,375 --> 00:12:01,375
a captain with
the Eastern Expedition.

230
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:03,416
Serafina de Lavillant!

231
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:06,625
And I refuse to beg for mercy!

232
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:09,625
Go on and sacrifice me,
you monster!

233
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:16,125
That's right.

234
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:18,291
They may rip the life from me,

235
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:20,208
but they'll never
take my dignity!

236
00:12:20,416 --> 00:12:21,875
[VEOR] Serafina.

237
00:12:22,083 --> 00:12:23,333
Sera, for short.

238
00:12:23,541 --> 00:12:24,666
A good strong name.

239
00:12:25,208 --> 00:12:26,458
But I do have to ask,

240
00:12:26,833 --> 00:12:29,333
what's all this talk
of sacrifice?

241
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,833
I only had one purpose
in capturing you.

242
00:12:34,041 --> 00:12:35,458
To make you my bride.

243
00:12:39,416 --> 00:12:40,875
[speechless]

244
00:12:42,375 --> 00:12:46,166
-Wait, what? Bride? Who, now?
-You, of course.

245
00:12:46,375 --> 00:12:47,791
-Whose bride?
-My bride.

246
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:49,416
You're lying!

247
00:12:50,458 --> 00:12:52,250
You can't deceive me!

248
00:12:52,458 --> 00:12:53,666
You want me docile,

249
00:12:53,666 --> 00:12:55,791
so you can use me
in your bizarre ritual!

250
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:59,416
If that was my true intention,
then why are you still alive?

251
00:12:59,625 --> 00:13:01,541
[SERAFINA] I don't know,
but you can't marry me,

252
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:03,208
we're sworn enemies!

253
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:05,041
And who says
you can't wed your enemy?

254
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:06,583
Everybody says that!

255
00:13:06,791 --> 00:13:08,791
[VEOR] Well, that may be
the case in the west,

256
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:11,708
but we clearly have different
customs here in the east.

257
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,333
Clearly.

258
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:18,375
You see, my clan has
a generations-long tradition.

259
00:13:19,375 --> 00:13:21,750
We find the most
exceptional lady knights

260
00:13:21,958 --> 00:13:24,666
and take them for our brides!

261
00:13:25,041 --> 00:13:27,375
[screaming]

262
00:13:27,583 --> 00:13:30,208
This is utter madness!

263
00:13:31,208 --> 00:13:33,166
Do you really think
your insane customs

264
00:13:33,375 --> 00:13:34,708
will convince me to marry you?

265
00:13:34,916 --> 00:13:36,041
Then you're not convinced?

266
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,458
Not at all!

267
00:13:38,666 --> 00:13:40,583
You were perfectly willing
to be sacrificed,

268
00:13:40,791 --> 00:13:43,333
but now you're saying
marriage is too much for you?

269
00:13:43,541 --> 00:13:44,750
[gasps]

270
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:47,708
Or were you merely
putting on a brave face?

271
00:13:48,416 --> 00:13:50,125
He's got me there.

272
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:53,541
[VEOR] And besides,
I haven't come to this decision

273
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:56,333
out of respect
for our laws or traditions.

274
00:13:56,875 --> 00:13:59,541
I felt it deep within me
when we crossed our swords.

275
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:00,833
[gasps]

276
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:02,708
A single blow with the sword

277
00:14:02,916 --> 00:14:04,833
can say more
than a thousand words.

278
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:08,791
You expressed a profound
sincerity with your blade.

279
00:14:10,166 --> 00:14:11,708
[speechless]

280
00:14:13,125 --> 00:14:15,125
And I fell for you right then.

281
00:14:16,708 --> 00:14:20,666
You fell for me?

282
00:14:22,416 --> 00:14:24,208
My feelings aside,

283
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:26,416
I won't take you
against your will,

284
00:14:26,625 --> 00:14:27,666
so you can relax.

285
00:14:28,458 --> 00:14:30,375
[VEOR] We'll speak later, Sera.

286
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:36,333
Come back! Just wait a moment!

287
00:14:38,041 --> 00:14:40,333
Wha. What.

288
00:14:40,541 --> 00:14:41,958
[gasps]

289
00:14:42,166 --> 00:14:44,750
[SERAFINA]
What is happening here?

290
00:14:44,958 --> 00:14:46,333
[CERSEI]
How is this not obvious?

291
00:14:46,541 --> 00:14:47,625
You're being courted.

292
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:56,208
ILLDOREN KINGDOM PROVINCE OF
MARGRAVE LAVILLANT EAU DE MARIE

293
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:59,333
SEVEN YEARS AGO

294
00:15:02,416 --> 00:15:04,541
[SIDIUS] We've received
orders from the king.

295
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:09,416
The Seventeenth Eastern
Expedition has been approved.

296
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:13,625
And you have been
honored, sister.

297
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:15,166
You are to serve as the captain

298
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:17,208
of the First Company,
it would seem.

299
00:15:20,291 --> 00:15:23,041
Acquire the glory
befitting the Lavillant name.

300
00:15:23,458 --> 00:15:24,666
I will!

301
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:28,250
[SIDIUS] Wait.

302
00:15:31,083 --> 00:15:32,875
We also received
a banquet invitation

303
00:15:33,083 --> 00:15:34,500
from Countess Ildhal.

304
00:15:35,541 --> 00:15:37,041
And why tell me?

305
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:40,000
Well, it's yours.

306
00:15:40,208 --> 00:15:42,125
Addressed
to "Princess" Serafina.

307
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,750
Right, then I shall attend.

308
00:15:54,583 --> 00:15:57,000
Someone grab that thieving kid!

309
00:15:57,625 --> 00:15:59,625
[CITIZEN] Pays well,
but is it worth it?

310
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:01,541
A pal of mine signed up
for the sixteenth

311
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:03,041
and never made it back.

312
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:04,958
Another expedition to the east?

313
00:16:05,416 --> 00:16:07,416
Well I'm definitely
volunteering!

314
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,708
Hey! It's the Lavillants' coach!

315
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:33,500
[NOBLE] How rare!

316
00:16:33,708 --> 00:16:35,416
Look who's chosen to attend.

317
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:37,000
Most rare indeed.

318
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:38,833
[sighs]

319
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:42,916
[NOBLE] The quality of food has
been so disappointing lately.

320
00:16:43,125 --> 00:16:46,250
The longer the war drags on,
the more we profit from it.

321
00:16:46,458 --> 00:16:47,500
Let's hope it never ends.

322
00:16:47,708 --> 00:16:49,458
[laughing]

323
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:53,333
[NOBLE] Princess Serafina
does cut quite the figure.

324
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,541
I don't know
if I'd call her beautiful,

325
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,500
but perhaps handsome?

326
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,875
To think she commands
our knights.

327
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:01,291
What a state of affairs.

328
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,041
Imagine being led by a woman.

329
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:04,875
Though, to give credit
where it's due,

330
00:17:05,083 --> 00:17:07,041
she is among the strongest
of the order.

331
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:08,958
And it is only natural
for a Lavillant

332
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:10,291
to command an army,

333
00:17:10,291 --> 00:17:13,500
but a strong woman
is just unnatural.

334
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:20,375
[sighs]

335
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:23,416
I want to go home.

336
00:17:24,458 --> 00:17:26,250
[ACQUAINTANCE ] Lady Serafina.

337
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:29,958
We've been searching
for you and here you are.

338
00:17:30,166 --> 00:17:31,916
You shouldn't be
out here on your own.

339
00:17:32,166 --> 00:17:34,083
Won't you come join us, please?

340
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:38,250
[ACQUAINTANCE ] It must have
been years since we last spoke.

341
00:17:38,875 --> 00:17:40,625
So is it true?

342
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:42,875
You were named a commander
for the Eastern Expedition?

343
00:17:43,083 --> 00:17:44,166
[SERAFINA] Yes.

344
00:17:44,375 --> 00:17:45,875
[ACQUAINTANCE ]
Oh, how dreadful!

345
00:17:46,083 --> 00:17:47,500
Isn't the east believed
to be teeming

346
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:50,000
with horribly vicious,
unknown creatures?

347
00:17:50,541 --> 00:17:52,458
I've heard whispers
of fire-breathing dragons

348
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:54,000
and other monsters.

349
00:17:54,208 --> 00:17:56,583
Those monsters
only exist in fables.

350
00:17:56,791 --> 00:17:59,458
[ACQUAINTANCE] But that doesn't
make it any less dangerous.

351
00:17:59,666 --> 00:18:02,125
The barbarians you're facing
are monstrous enough.

352
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:05,000
I've heard they're barely
more than savage beasts

353
00:18:05,208 --> 00:18:06,541
in the form of humans.

354
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:09,875
And they abduct lady knights
to sacrifice them!

355
00:18:10,083 --> 00:18:12,375
If the Eastern lands
are truly that terrible,

356
00:18:12,583 --> 00:18:15,125
a woman should
avoid them at all costs.

357
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:21,083
Conquering and claiming the east
has been our objective

358
00:18:21,291 --> 00:18:23,333
since the founding
of this kingdom.

359
00:18:23,541 --> 00:18:26,416
As a member of the nobility,
it is an honor to be sent there.

360
00:18:26,625 --> 00:18:29,375
I will gladly fight for
the prosperity of our people.

361
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:32,000
[ACQUAINTANCE ]
But that really is the sort

362
00:18:32,208 --> 00:18:33,416
of thing a man should handle.

363
00:18:33,416 --> 00:18:35,291
What chance could
a woman possibly have

364
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,916
for a favorable outcome?

365
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:39,791
Even Princess Wysteresia,
whom you so idolized,

366
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,083
wound up going missing
on the battlefield.

367
00:18:43,125 --> 00:18:45,041
I believe the greatest honor
for a woman

368
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:47,291
is to get married
and manage her household.

369
00:18:48,375 --> 00:18:49,875
[scoffs]

370
00:18:54,916 --> 00:18:56,791
They have it so easy.

371
00:18:57,625 --> 00:19:00,291
Gorging themselves
and dancing the night away.

372
00:19:05,166 --> 00:19:07,291
All while our crops
keep failing,

373
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:09,291
and the people
begin to slowly starve.

374
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:11,750
[MERCHANT] No! Someone help me!

375
00:19:12,250 --> 00:19:15,833
[screaming]

376
00:19:18,958 --> 00:19:20,250
[SERAFINA] That's quite enough!

377
00:19:20,458 --> 00:19:21,833
[gasps]

378
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:25,000
Try resisting and I won't
guarantee your lives.

379
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:28,375
[SERAFINA] They look terrified.

380
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:32,916
[gasps] That's a noble sword.

381
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:34,375
So? It don't matter!

382
00:19:34,583 --> 00:19:35,958
We've got no choice!

383
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,250
You're no bandits.

384
00:19:46,458 --> 00:19:48,750
You've never stooped
to this before, have you?

385
00:19:48,958 --> 00:19:49,916
[fearful]

386
00:19:50,125 --> 00:19:51,916
It's this or starve to death!

387
00:19:52,125 --> 00:19:53,375
You wouldn't understand!

388
00:20:02,666 --> 00:20:04,000
[disbelief]

389
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:06,166
Promise that you'll harm
no one else.

390
00:20:06,375 --> 00:20:09,041
-Wait. We can have that?
-Yes.

391
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:11,250
Oh, wow! Thank you, ma'am!

392
00:20:11,458 --> 00:20:13,833
I'll actually be able
to feed my kid now!

393
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,541
We will never do this again.

394
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:20,208
-[BANDIT 1] Come on.
-[BANDIT 2] Yeah.

395
00:20:22,291 --> 00:20:23,875
[BANDIT 2] We owe her our lives.

396
00:20:24,083 --> 00:20:25,250
[BANDIT 1] No kidding!

397
00:20:26,458 --> 00:20:28,750
Please just try to endure.

398
00:20:29,083 --> 00:20:30,833
I will conquer the east.

399
00:20:32,375 --> 00:20:35,208
So that you can live the lives
that you deserve.

400
00:20:35,791 --> 00:20:38,916
[gentle music playing]

401
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:44,791
[SERAFINA] The time has come.

402
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,708
I will fight with all I have,

403
00:20:46,916 --> 00:20:50,500
for the people and the kingdom,
Princess Wysteresia.

404
00:20:52,708 --> 00:20:54,166
Watch over me.

405
00:20:54,375 --> 00:20:55,583
[SIDIUS] Serafina.

406
00:20:58,708 --> 00:21:00,000
Hello, Brother.

407
00:21:00,291 --> 00:21:01,666
You failed to find a husband

408
00:21:01,875 --> 00:21:03,333
for yourself
at the party, I see.

409
00:21:03,541 --> 00:21:04,666
I what?

410
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:06,583
But why would I
even be looking for one?

411
00:21:06,791 --> 00:21:08,958
-I was on the verge of going--
-[SIDIUS] Silence.

412
00:21:09,166 --> 00:21:11,041
A woman posing
as a knight of the realm.

413
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:13,291
How long will
this selfishness last?

414
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:14,958
[SERAFINA] What are you saying?

415
00:21:15,166 --> 00:21:16,041
You have made your point,

416
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:17,666
now it's time to stop.

417
00:21:17,875 --> 00:21:19,916
You must marry
before you're too old.

418
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:22,000
A sword won't change policy.

419
00:21:22,208 --> 00:21:24,958
Sera.

420
00:21:25,166 --> 00:21:30,541
Sera. Sera. Sera!

421
00:21:30,750 --> 00:21:33,750
[VEOR] I will take you
as my bride!

422
00:21:33,958 --> 00:21:35,958
[shocked] It's you!

423
00:21:36,166 --> 00:21:40,708
You are meant to be my bride!

424
00:21:40,916 --> 00:21:42,125
[gasps]

425
00:21:43,208 --> 00:21:44,791
[jolting awake]

426
00:21:46,583 --> 00:21:49,625
Just a dream
about the barbarian?

427
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:50,958
Why?

428
00:21:51,166 --> 00:21:52,416
[sighs]

429
00:21:53,041 --> 00:21:55,000
[VEOR snoring]

430
00:21:55,208 --> 00:21:56,916
Where's that sound coming.

431
00:21:57,166 --> 00:21:58,750
From?

432
00:22:12,208 --> 00:22:14,291
THE WARRIOR PRINCESS
AND THE BARBARIC KING

433
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:18,833
[♪ upbeat music playing,
Sajou no Hana "Shirubeki Koto"]
